{
  "stem": "9665.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "In your late teens, towards 1939, what did you know of what was happening in the rest of Europe?",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That-- what was happening where?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In the rest of Europe.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In the rest of Europe, we knew about it.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The newspapers, the radio.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were not aware-- we were aware that the Jews were not treated well, but our feeling was, in Holland, that Holland has been neutral in the first World War.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Whatever is going to happen now, Holland is going to be neutral.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I think the people in Belgium-- and I went up and down to Antwerp every few months-- were of the same opinion.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] We were convinced that we will stay out of the war.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we had the same feeling as what the Dutch, what the German Jews had towards the Polish Jews that they thought, the Germans, nothing will happen to us.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It's the Polish Jews which were expelled from Germany in the Nazi time.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I think the Dutch Jews had that same feeling.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It was that they were not even against the German Jews, against the Polish Jews, which came to us, or wanted to escape or were waiting for a visa to go to America, or to South America, or to Canada.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Some of the Jews which came over illegally were put in a camp in Holland, but it wasn't what you would call a concentration camp.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] It was a camp more for transit.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "If they were caught close to the border, they were sent back to Germany, and that wasn't really very nice.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we felt very angry about it, but what could we do?",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
